sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pUV + NhaS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: NhaS with an RFP reporter induced by an UV promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
NhaS with an RFP reporter induced by an UV promoter.
This device is activated when UV promoter (BBa_I765001) is exposed to 360nm of UV irradiation. It produces a gene called NhaS (BBa_K1255000) that is a sodium ion binding protein and reports its function with a red fluorescence reporter. (BBa_E1010) It contains an RBS (BBa_B0034) before its genes.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Fernanda Puente, Marina Emilio
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: RFP comes from Discosoma striata (coral) and NhaS from Bacillus firms
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: NhaS (BBa_K1255000) sequence was optimized for its expression in E. coli

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: nhaS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: nhaS gene that express NhaS, a putative sodium ion binding protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
"NhaS is proposed to be a sodium binding protein that can enhance the Na+ -resistance of antiporter- deficient strains by increasing the availability of Na+ to the integral membrane antiporters on the cytoplasmic side of the membrane and by sequestering Na+ while rate-limiting efflux mechanisms catalyze extrusion of the cation." (Krulwich et al. 1994)
"The NhaS protein enhances resistance of bacteria into which the nhaS gene has been introduced, to Na+ by sequestering Na+ and reducing its cytotoxicity." (Krulwich et al. 1994)
NhaS is protein that binds to sodium ions and enhance the bacteria's resistance up to 15% to high saline conditions.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Fernanda Puente, Marina Emilio
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
The original genomic sequence was optimized for expression in E. coli.
IVEY Mark, KRULWICH Terry. (1994) Sodium ion binding proteins. From http://www.google.com.mx/patents/US5346815.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: monomeric RFP: Red Fluorescent Protein. Excitation peak: 584 nm Emission peak: 607 nm
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Campbell et al., PNAS v99 p7877 URL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
TAATAA double stop codon added (DE).
Four silent mutations made to remove three EcoRI sites and one PstI site: A28G, A76G, A349G, G337A.
